[The risk to dairy cattle of a tubercular stockman is a long recognised
problem. In this instance it would be of value to know the positive rates
for animal handlers not working with elephants (but who had presumably been
in social contact with the active human case), and the reactor rate for
elephants on the exotic animal farm which had not toured with the
circus-four survivors. Similarly, how many negative elephants had positive
handlers, and vice versa. These data would give a better appreciation of the
lateral spread risks from actively infected human(s) and elephants. mod MHJ
